-- Czech Telecom Regulator to Cut Termination Fees in July, HN Says
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-03-19T08:53:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/czech-telecom-regulator-to-cut-termination-fees-in-july-hn-says.html
The Czech Republic’s
telecommunication regulator, CTU, plans to cut termination fees
for telecommunication operators from 1.08 koruna ($0.05) to 0.55
koruna a minute beginning in July,  Pravo  reported, citing the
regulator’s spokesman, Frantisek Malina.  The regulator started administration proceedings about the
cut with the Czech units of  Vodafone Group Plc (VOD) , T-Mobile
International AG and  Telefonica SA (TEF) , the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
